# Portfolio — Project Context

Single **landing page**: About, Toolkit, Projects, and Contact are stacked sections on one scrollable `index.html`. Nav links smooth-scroll to `#about`, `#toolkit`, `#projects`, `#contact`.

## Directory structure

```
portfolio/
├── .cursorfile           # This file — project rules & layout
├── index.html            # Landing page: header + 4 sections + footer
├── prd.md                # Product requirements document
├── css/
│   └── style.css         # Custom CSS (scrollbar, toolkit hovers, projects rail, form)
└── js/
    ├── theme-init.js     # Sync in <head> — apply saved theme before paint
    ├── tailwind-config.js
    ├── navigation.js     # Smooth scroll, mobile menu, scroll-spy nav highlight
    ├── theme.js          # Theme toggle button
    └── contact.js        # Web3Forms contact submission
```

## Sections (all visible)


| Section  | ID        | Anchor     |
|----------|-----------|------------|
| About    | `#about`  | Top hero   |
| Toolkit  | `#toolkit`| After About|
| Project  | `#project`| after toolkit and before contact|
| Contact  | `#contact`| Before footer |

Use `scroll-mt-32 lg:scroll-mt-40` on sections so content clears the fixed header.

## Projects section

- Horizontal rail: `.projects-rail` with toolkit-style `.project-card` articles
- Scroll: native `overflow-x-auto` + scroll-snap (no JS carousel in v1)
- Cards: display-only (title, description, tech tags); no links unless added later

## Conventions

- **Tailwind**: CDN with `forms`, `container-queries`, `typography`. Config in `js/tailwind-config.js`. Base `@layer` rules stay in `index.html` as `<style type="text/tailwindcss">`.
- **No inline scripts** in `index.html` except AdSense if required — use `js/*.js`.
- **Paths**: Always relative to `portfolio/` (`css/`, `js/`).
- **Theme**: `localStorage.theme` = `light` | `dark`. Init in `theme-init.js`, toggle in `theme.js`.
- **Do not** hide sections with JS — this is one page, not tab routing.

## Adding a new section

1. Add `<section id="{name}" class="scroll-mt-32 lg:scroll-mt-40 ...">` in `index.html`.
2. Register `{name}` in `SECTIONS` in `js/navigation.js`.
3. Add `href="#{name}" data-nav="{name}"` in header (desktop + mobile).

## External dependencies

- Tailwind CDN, Google Fonts (Inter, Lora, Playfair Display, JetBrains Mono), Material Symbols
- Web3Forms API (`contact.js`)
